.TH "device_add_software_node" 9 "device_add_software_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
device_add_software_node \- Assign software node to a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" device_add_software_node
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct software_node *node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The device the software node is meant for.
.IP "node" 12
The software node.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will make \fInode\fP the secondary firmware node pointer of \fIdev\fP. If
\fIdev\fP has no primary node, then \fInode\fP will become the primary node. The
function will register \fInode\fP automatically if it wasn't already registered.
